Package: vldaft
Title: Non-Proportional Hazards Accelerated Failure Time Regression
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits the Anderson (1991) accelerated failure time regression model
    where both location and scale are functions of covariates, and scale can
    depend on location via theta polynomial parameters. Supports Weibull,
    logistic, normal, Cauchy, and gamma error distributions with right
    censoring, left censoring, and left truncation. Provides a standalone
    fitting function and gamlss2 family extensions.
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://keaven.github.io/vldaft/
NeedsCompilation: yes
SystemRequirements: Cargo (Rust's package manager), rustc
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: survival, stats
Suggests: gamlss2, knitr, litedown, rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: litedown, knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
